        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"markus.pilman\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"2358\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/48/379_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> markus.pilman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This is great! I really like the idea of having a stateless service that just provides the functionality of a layer (and if I understand this correctly, this is what you\u2019re doing?).</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thanks a lot! You are right, thanks to fdb, it is a stateless Vertx app running on top of FDB <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"markus.pilman\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"2358\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/markus.pilman/48/379_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> markus.pilman:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>It is a powerful concept, and you can even use <code>fdbmonitor</code> to start your record-store servers</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Ooooooh, looks like fun, I will try it <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/smile.png?v=12\" title=\":smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"> Thanks!</p>",
